statements: SELECT * FROM feature_engineering_results;
SELECT id, feature_1, target_variable FROM feature_engineering_results;
SELECT feature_3, feature_2 FROM feature_engineering_results;
SELECT feature_1, feature_2, feature_3, target_variable FROM feature_engineering_results WHERE id=1;
SELECT id, feature_1, feature_3, target_variable FROM feature_engineering_results WHERE feature_2 > 0.5;
SELECT * FROM feature_engineering_results WHERE feature_1 > 0.5 ORDER BY feature_1 DESC, id ASC LIMIT 10;
SELECT feature_2, target_variable FROM feature_engineering_results WHERE feature_2 BETWEEN 0.3 AND 0.6 ORDER BY target_variable ASC;
SELECT MAX(feature_3), MIN(target_variable) FROM feature_engineering_results;
SELECT AVG(feature_1), SUM(target_variable) FROM feature_engineering_results GROUP BY feature_1 HAVING AVG(feature_1) > 0.4;
SELECT id, feature_1, feature_2, target_variable FROM feature_engineering_results WHERE target_variable > 1.0 ORDER BY id DESC LIMIT 5;
SELECT * FROM RegressionModelResults;
SELECT feature_name, feature_value FROM RegressionModelResults WHERE target_variable > 0;
SELECT feature_name, target_variable FROM RegressionModelResults ORDER BY target_variable DESC;
SELECT model_name, training_date, accuracy FROM RegressionModelMetadata WHERE accuracy >= 0.8;
SELECT model_name, accuracy FROM RegressionModelMetadata WHERE training_date > '2022-01-01';
SELECT id, feature_name, feature_value, target_variable FROM RegressionModelResults WHERE feature_name = 'A' ORDER BY feature_value DESC LIMIT 10
SELECT feature_name, AVG(feature_value) AS avg_value, MAX(target_variable) AS max_target FROM RegressionModelResults GROUP BY feature_name
SELECT model_name, accuracy FROM RegressionModelMetadata WHERE training_date BETWEEN '2021-01-01' AND '2021-12-31' ORDER BY accuracy DESC
SELECT model_id, model_name, training_date FROM RegressionModelMetadata ORDER BY training_date ASC LIMIT 5
SELECT id, feature_name, feature_value, target_variable FROM RegressionModelResults WHERE target_variable > 0.5 ORDER BY feature_name
SELECT * FROM feature_engineering_results ORDER BY id DESC;
SELECT feature_name, feature_value FROM feature_engineering_results WHERE feature_value > 0.5;
SELECT model_name, metric_name, metric_value FROM model_metrics WHERE metric_value BETWEEN 0.1 AND 0.5;
SELECT model_name, param_name, param_value FROM model_params WHERE param_value = 0.2 ORDER BY model_name ASC;
SELECT id, feature_name, is_numerical FROM feature_engineering_results WHERE is_numerical = TRUE;
SELECT * FROM feature_engineering_results WHERE is_numerical = TRUE ORDER BY feature_name DESC;
SELECT feature_name, AVG(feature_value) AS avg_value FROM feature_engineering_results GROUP BY feature_name HAVING AVG(feature_value) > 0.5;
SELECT m.model_name, p.param_name, p.param_value FROM model_params p JOIN model_metrics m ON p.model_name = m.model_name WHERE m.metric_name = 'accuracy' ORDER BY p.param_value DESC;
SELECT MAX(feature_value) AS max_value, MIN(feature_value) AS min_value FROM feature_engineering_results;
SELECT model_name, COUNT(*) AS num_params FROM model_params GROUP BY model_name HAVING COUNT(*) > 2 ORDER BY num_params ASC;
SELECT * FROM FeatureEngineeringResults;
SELECT feature_name, feature_value FROM FeatureEngineeringResults WHERE feature_value > 0.5;
SELECT * FROM ModelMetrics ORDER BY metric_timestamp DESC;
SELECT id, setting_name, setting_value FROM ModelSettings WHERE setting_description LIKE '%parameter%';
SELECT * FROM ModelPrediction WHERE prediction_date BETWEEN '2021-01-01' AND '2021-12-31';
SELECT * FROM FeatureEngineeringResults WHERE feature_value > 0.5 ORDER BY feature_name DESC
SELECT metric_name, AVG(metric_value) as avg_value FROM ModelMetrics GROUP BY metric_name
SELECT setting_name, setting_value FROM ModelSettings WHERE setting_description LIKE '%important%'
SELECT model_id, prediction_value, prediction_date FROM ModelPrediction WHERE model_id = 100 ORDER BY prediction_date ASC
SELECT * FROM FeatureEngineeringResults WHERE feature_set = 'set1'
SELECT * FROM DataSources;
SELECT source_name, data_type FROM DataSources ORDER BY data_type DESC;
SELECT id, source_name, data_type FROM DataSources WHERE id > 3;
SELECT * FROM ModelParameters WHERE parameter_name='learning_rate';
SELECT model_id, parameter_name, parameter_value FROM ModelParameters WHERE model_id=2;

SELECT model_name, model_type FROM RegressionModel WHERE model_type = 'linear regression'
SELECT model_id, metric_name, metric_value FROM ModelEvaluation WHERE metric_value > 0.8 ORDER BY metric_value DESC
